lore synopsis — edge-keyed synopsis sidecar management

Usage: lore synopsis <subcommand> [args...]

Subcommands:
  get <entry_id> <requesting_scale>
                           Output cached synopsis (exit 0), exit 1 if not found,
                           exit 2 if stale (parent hash or template_version changed)
  put <entry_id> <requesting_scale> --content-file <path> --parent-hash <hex> --parent-template-version <ver> --status <cached|generated|fallback>
                           Write synopsis sidecar, print path on stdout
  invalidate <entry_id>
                           Delete all synopsis cache files for entry_id (all scales);
                           prints deleted count on stdout

Storage: \$KDIR/_edge_synopses/<sanitized_entry_id>__<requesting_scale>.md
The sanitized_entry_id is the entry's relative path with '/' → '__'.

Options:
  --help, -h    Show this help
EOF
}

